Let $Q(h, O)$<br><br>
$\because $ OP reflected by $x+y=1$.<br><br>
So, image of $Q$ lies on $y=\frac{x}{\sqrt{3}}$<br><br>
$$
\begin{aligned}
&amp; \therefore \quad \frac{x-h}{1}=\frac{y}{1}=\frac{-2(h-1)}{2} \\\\
&amp; \therefore \quad x=1, y=1-h
\end{aligned}
$$<br><br>
It lies on $y=\frac{x}{\sqrt{3}}$<br><br>
$$
\begin{aligned}
&amp; \therefore \quad 1-h=\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} \\\\
&amp; \therefore \quad h=1-\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}=\frac{\sqrt{3}-1}{\sqrt{3}}=\frac{2}{3+\sqrt{3}}
\end{aligned}
$$
